WEBVTT

00:01.131 --> 00:03.133
Previously on "Manifest"...

00:03.177 --> 00:04.178
I think something bad
is gonna happen.

00:04.221 --> 00:07.007
-Marko?
-To him and me.

00:07.050 --> 00:08.573
What are you
doing here, Vance?

00:08.617 --> 00:09.835
We need each other.

00:09.879 --> 00:11.359
-We do this in two steps.
-Right.

00:11.402 --> 00:14.318
Plant the bug. And, uh, then
we give them a little nudge.

00:14.362 --> 00:16.842
Somebody did a search,
network-wide.

00:16.886 --> 00:19.062
"Experiments"
and "Flight 828."

00:19.106 --> 00:20.498
It worked.

00:20.542 --> 00:21.717
We've already moved them
to Brooklyn...

00:21.760 --> 00:23.545
all 11,
to the clean room.

00:23.588 --> 00:26.156
Harvey, I'm a cop, and
I was on the plane with you.

00:26.200 --> 00:27.331
It has to stop.

00:27.375 --> 00:29.072
Harvey, no! No!

00:29.116 --> 00:31.509
He told people
about his callings.

00:31.553 --> 00:33.033
Two of those people died.

00:33.076 --> 00:35.035
I told Grace.
You told Jared.

00:35.078 --> 00:38.038
[ Electricity crackles,
high-pitched buzzing ]

00:38.081 --> 00:40.562
-You left me alone.
-I'm sorry.

00:40.605 --> 00:42.346
You can't ever
do that again.

00:42.390 --> 00:43.869
That's an incredibly
powerful weapon --

00:43.913 --> 00:45.567
for the military,
for intelligence.

00:45.610 --> 00:48.396
This time,
he might not survive.

00:52.574 --> 00:54.967
[ Rumbling,
passengers screaming ]

00:56.317 --> 01:01.104
Autumn: It was awful.
The whole plane was shaking.

01:01.148 --> 01:03.367
It felt like
we were gonna crash.

01:03.411 --> 01:06.631
The emergency path lights
came on, and then...

01:08.285 --> 01:09.808
...we landed.

01:09.852 --> 01:11.462
It makes no sense.

01:11.506 --> 01:13.943
We'll have to run some tests,
to clear you to leave.

01:13.986 --> 01:15.727
My son has leukemia.

01:15.771 --> 01:17.903
He's not about to submit
to testing of any kind.

01:17.947 --> 01:19.644
I need to make a call, okay?
I need --

01:19.688 --> 01:22.125
I need to call my boyf--
my fiancé.

01:22.169 --> 01:23.953
We're releasing
everyone tomorrow.

01:23.996 --> 01:26.086
We need the name
of the person or persons

01:26.129 --> 01:27.957
you want to authorize
to pick you up.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.220
I, uh, I don't
really have anyone.

01:30.264 --> 01:32.918
I'm kind of between
"persons" right now.

01:32.962 --> 01:34.790
I'll just get a cab
or something.

01:34.833 --> 01:38.098
Well, actually, Ms. Cox,
it seems you have

01:38.141 --> 01:41.449
several outstanding warrants
for your arrest.

01:41.492 --> 01:43.146
She's all yours.

01:43.190 --> 01:46.802
No, y-you don't understand.
I didn't do any of those things!

01:46.845 --> 01:49.196
Wait!
Please let me explain!

01:49.239 --> 01:52.329
[ Engines roaring ]

01:58.030 --> 02:01.295
The detainees are likely
being held in this warehouse,

02:01.338 --> 02:03.732
built before the Civil War,
used for storage.

02:03.775 --> 02:07.736
Perimeter has some security,
but I...

02:07.779 --> 02:09.738
Why are you leaving?
-No, why aren't youleaving?

02:09.781 --> 02:12.001
We have an address.
We know where the missing
passengers are.

02:12.044 --> 02:13.350
We have to get them --Whoa.

02:13.394 --> 02:15.047
You people rushed in there
at the farm,

02:15.091 --> 02:16.658
and the detainees
were disappeared.

02:16.701 --> 02:19.139
May I suggest we take a beat
to do this the right way?

02:21.706 --> 02:24.753
Starting with Laurence Belson,
face of the Singularity Project.

02:24.796 --> 02:27.364
We have an office address,
e-mail -- that's it.

02:27.408 --> 02:28.844
We need more.

02:28.887 --> 02:30.846
I'll go into work,
see what I can dig up.

02:30.889 --> 02:34.763
Hey. Take this burner.
Let me know what you find.

02:36.156 --> 02:38.332
What can I do?

02:38.375 --> 02:40.334
It's Saturday. Go home.
Be with your family.

02:40.377 --> 02:42.858
Anything comes up, I'll contact
you on your burner.

02:42.901 --> 02:45.556
What, so I'm supposed to
just wait?
Yes.

02:45.600 --> 02:47.602
Those experiments can
start up at any moment.

02:47.645 --> 02:49.604
You are a piece of work.

02:49.647 --> 02:52.259
It is my job to make sure
this mission is successful.

02:52.302 --> 02:55.436
I assure you I will go in
the second I can do it cleanly

02:55.479 --> 02:57.873
without tipping them off
that we're coming again

02:57.916 --> 02:59.918
and without loss of life.

03:01.311 --> 03:03.879
Grace: [ Softly ] This is
top secret, got it?

03:03.922 --> 03:05.707
-[ Softly ] Got it.
-Are you sure?

03:05.750 --> 03:07.622
Because this is
very serious business,

03:07.665 --> 03:09.754
and I'm counting on you.Got it.

03:09.798 --> 03:13.889
What are you two
whispering about?

03:13.932 --> 03:17.719
Well...your dad's
been working so hard,

03:17.762 --> 03:19.460
and he hasn't really
caught up with his friends

03:19.503 --> 03:23.072
since he's been back,
so I decided to throw him

03:23.115 --> 03:26.815
a last-minute surprise
backyard barbecue today.

03:26.858 --> 03:29.948
And you and I have to keep Dad
out of the house until 4:30.

03:29.992 --> 03:31.776
Ah. Sneaky.
I like it.

03:31.820 --> 03:33.691
Yeah?

03:37.129 --> 03:40.263
Hi!
You were out early.

03:40.307 --> 03:42.265
I had to get a new phone.
I dropped mine.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.701
Same number, no bigs.

03:45.486 --> 03:48.663
So, uh, Dad, Cal wants to go
laser tagging this afternoon.

03:48.706 --> 03:49.925
Can you take us?

03:49.968 --> 03:52.406
Yeah.
Yeah, but I'm playing.

03:52.449 --> 03:55.583
[ Cellphone ringing ]

03:55.626 --> 03:57.759
What's up?

03:57.802 --> 04:00.675
Uh, it's work
looking for me.

04:00.718 --> 04:03.286
Oh, no. Don't tell me
they're gonna make you
come in on the weekend.

04:03.330 --> 04:05.201
Not if I don't answer.[ Ringing stops ]

04:05.245 --> 04:07.290
I like your style.

04:07.334 --> 04:08.683
All right. I got errands.

04:08.726 --> 04:11.163
Kids, please take it easy
on your old dad.

04:11.207 --> 04:13.862
-Hey!
-[ Laughs ]

04:13.905 --> 04:15.342
All right, so,
let's head out in a bit.

04:15.385 --> 04:17.300
We have to be back
around, like, 4:30.

04:17.344 --> 04:18.954
Avery's picking me up.

04:18.997 --> 04:21.130
Yeah, that should give me plenty
of time to defeat you two.

04:21.173 --> 04:23.001
[ Laughs ]

04:24.394 --> 04:25.700
You gonna go
shoot some hoops?

04:25.743 --> 04:27.832
Tryouts on Monday.
I thought maybe I'd...

04:27.876 --> 04:29.312
Cal, why didn't you
tell me?

04:29.356 --> 04:31.140
I could've been
warming you up all week.

04:31.183 --> 04:33.011
You haven't
been around much.

04:34.361 --> 04:36.667
[ Sighs ]
Well, I-I'm here now.

04:40.018 --> 04:42.630
Ah. Closer.
Caught some backboard.

04:42.673 --> 04:44.327
You know that's not the point
of the game, right, Dad?

04:44.371 --> 04:45.676
Don't be so hard
on yourself.

04:45.720 --> 04:47.809
Some of the other kids
trying out for the league

04:47.852 --> 04:49.637
have been playing
for years.

04:49.680 --> 04:51.334
Well, you've been
a little busy.

04:51.378 --> 04:53.336
Traveling through space and
time, kicking cancer's butt.

04:53.380 --> 04:55.556
Let's go.
[ Laughs ]

04:55.599 --> 04:56.992
-Oh! [ Laughs ]
-Yes!

04:57.035 --> 05:00.082
LeBron better
watch his back.

05:03.215 --> 05:05.392
Hey, buddy,
wanna take a break?

05:05.435 --> 05:07.742
-Can I have screen time?
-Yeah, sure.

05:07.785 --> 05:12.660
♪♪

05:12.703 --> 05:14.966
Ben Stone?
Please help me.

05:23.627 --> 05:26.587
[ Breathing shakily ]
Thank you.

05:26.630 --> 05:29.764
I'm -- My name is Autumn.

05:29.807 --> 05:31.766
Autumn Cox.
From the plane, right?

05:33.420 --> 05:35.073
How did you find me?

05:35.117 --> 05:37.989
I heard your name.

05:38.033 --> 05:40.165
Like my own voice
in my head.

05:40.209 --> 05:43.081
And somehow I knew
instinctively how to get here.

05:43.125 --> 05:44.474
Is that crazy?

05:44.518 --> 05:46.607
No, actually.

05:46.650 --> 05:50.088
It was like my subconscious was
telling me that you could help.

05:50.132 --> 05:51.960
Here.
[ Groans ]

05:56.965 --> 06:00.360
Maybe I can.

06:00.403 --> 06:05.408
Can you tell me what happened
to you and the others?

06:05.452 --> 06:10.413
They kept us
hooked up to monitors,

06:10.457 --> 06:12.937
took samples of our blood.

06:12.981 --> 06:15.940
They ran all kinds
of tests on us.

06:15.984 --> 06:18.813
Autumn, who are "they"?

06:18.856 --> 06:21.206
I don't know.

06:21.250 --> 06:23.818
We were drugged
most of the time.

06:23.861 --> 06:26.168
I finally managed to spit
my pills out and escape

06:26.211 --> 06:27.952
when they brought us
somewhere in a van.

06:27.996 --> 06:30.128
Do you know where
the others are?

06:30.172 --> 06:32.783
I-I tried to remember
everything I could.

06:32.827 --> 06:36.004
Um, there is a long road.

06:36.047 --> 06:38.789
And it's rural.
There's no car noises.

06:38.833 --> 06:41.444
And it smelled
like fertilizer.

06:41.488 --> 06:43.620
And a red door.
I remember that.

06:43.664 --> 06:44.969
The dairy farm.

06:45.013 --> 06:46.536
I think I could
find my way back.

06:46.580 --> 06:49.234
We already have.
It was empty.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.802
Autumn, you said
you escaped from a van.

06:51.846 --> 06:54.196
Do you know
where it was going?

06:54.239 --> 06:58.026
No. Oh, God. I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

06:58.069 --> 07:02.726
No. It's okay. We just
need to get you some help.

07:02.770 --> 07:03.988
[ Dialing ]Who are you calling?

07:04.032 --> 07:06.077
-My sister. She's a cop.
-No! No!

07:06.121 --> 07:09.341
There were warrants out for my
arrest when I got off the plane,

07:09.385 --> 07:11.169
but the police
who took me from the hangar

07:11.213 --> 07:13.084
were the ones who
turned me over to them.

07:13.128 --> 07:14.999
No, it's okay. Michaela's
one of us, a passenger,

07:15.043 --> 07:16.479
and so is the doctor
I want you to see.

07:16.523 --> 07:18.481
I promise you it's okay.

07:18.525 --> 07:21.397
We're all in this together.
You're safe now.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.181
[ Ringing]

07:23.225 --> 07:26.010
[ Cellphone ringing ]

07:26.054 --> 07:28.709
Hey. Good timing.
I've got the warehouse plans.

07:28.752 --> 07:31.668
And I've got a missing
passenger. In my garage.

07:31.712 --> 07:33.191
What?

07:33.235 --> 07:36.020
Autumn Cox. The one
the prison system misplaced.

07:36.064 --> 07:37.500
Ben, you got to
get her out of there.

07:37.544 --> 07:39.023
What if Laurence Belson
comes looking for --

07:39.067 --> 07:40.677
Take her
to the boiler room.

07:40.721 --> 07:43.680
Yeah, good call. I'll have
Saanvi and Fiona meet me there.

07:43.724 --> 07:46.030
Okay. Keep me posted.

07:46.074 --> 07:47.902
Cal: Bad stuff
is about to happen.

07:47.945 --> 07:50.600
[ Tablet game beeping]I'm the commander now.

07:50.644 --> 07:53.211
Uh, guys,
I hate to do this,

07:53.255 --> 07:55.300
but something came up
with work after all.

07:55.344 --> 07:57.433
I'm gonna have to
postpone laser tag.

07:57.477 --> 07:59.087
But you'll be home
by 4:30, right?

07:59.130 --> 08:00.741
Yeah, Avery wants you
to see his new car

08:00.784 --> 08:02.743
when he comes
to pick me up.I'll do my best.

08:02.786 --> 08:04.484
You gotta, Dad!

08:04.527 --> 08:06.486
Okay. 4:30.

08:09.140 --> 08:12.709
[ Tablet game beeping]

08:12.753 --> 08:14.232
I love you guys.

08:14.276 --> 08:16.713
-Love you, too, Dad.
-Same.

08:16.757 --> 08:18.715
Stop.

08:18.759 --> 08:21.283
[ Beeping continues]

08:24.504 --> 08:26.723
Hey.

08:26.767 --> 08:28.943
What are you hiding
from me now?

08:28.986 --> 08:31.293
Uh, nothing.

08:31.336 --> 08:33.730
You'd tell me if someone else
who heard the callings

08:33.774 --> 08:34.949
drops dead, right?

08:34.992 --> 08:36.559
That's not funny, Jared.

08:36.603 --> 08:38.953
I know, Mick.

08:38.996 --> 08:40.824
And if you're in danger,

08:40.868 --> 08:45.133
you have to tell me,
no matter what.

08:45.176 --> 08:47.657
Okay, look, I'll take that risk.
I don't care.

08:47.701 --> 08:50.051
I do, okay? I do care.

08:50.094 --> 08:55.839
♪♪

08:55.883 --> 08:59.495
Clarke: My God. How awful.
Hello, Autumn. I'm Fiona.

08:59.539 --> 09:02.237
I'm really sorry for everything
you've been through,

09:02.280 --> 09:05.545
and I assure you we're
going to help the others.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.329
Saanvi:
We should get her some rest.

09:11.115 --> 09:14.031
Are those burn marks part
of your research protocol?

09:14.075 --> 09:15.903
Clarke:
Electrotherapy.

09:15.946 --> 09:19.994
To activate mirror neurons
in the premotor cortex.

09:20.037 --> 09:21.648
-Meaning?
-Meaning that they need

09:21.691 --> 09:23.911
to get at something
inside their heads,

09:23.954 --> 09:26.000
but i-instead of
picking the lock,

09:26.043 --> 09:28.437
they are using dynamite
to blast the door down.

09:28.480 --> 09:30.744
You had no idea
what you were doing.

09:30.787 --> 09:34.051
Oh, my God.Your research
is wildly unethical.

09:34.095 --> 09:36.010
It was theoretical.

09:36.053 --> 09:38.839
A way to increase
human connection.

09:38.882 --> 09:40.580
I never intended for it
to be used this way.

09:40.623 --> 09:42.538
Then you shouldn't have
handed over your research.

09:42.582 --> 09:45.628
Neuroscience
is an arms race.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.935
The government doesn't care
about who gets hurt

09:47.978 --> 09:49.632
as long as they
get results.

09:49.676 --> 09:51.068
Not the wholegovernment.

09:51.112 --> 09:55.029
Vance. This is the proof
he's been waiting for.

09:55.072 --> 09:58.119
-We should bring him in.
-No! He put Bethany in jail.

09:58.162 --> 10:00.208
If Autumn has a warrant out for
her arrest, he'll do the same.

10:00.251 --> 10:02.558
Do you really want him
knowing about this place?

10:02.602 --> 10:03.907
We need his help.

10:03.951 --> 10:06.040
Vance risked his career
by trusting me.

10:06.083 --> 10:07.607
It's time
for us to trust him.

10:07.650 --> 10:09.521
Autumn: It's okay.

10:11.436 --> 10:14.309
I don't want to go to jail,

10:14.352 --> 10:18.922
but you haven't seen
what they're doing to us.

10:18.966 --> 10:21.969
I'll do whatever I have to.

10:22.012 --> 10:29.150
♪♪

10:29.193 --> 10:36.331
♪♪

10:36.374 --> 10:43.512
♪♪

10:43.555 --> 10:45.993
Vance: My God.

10:46.036 --> 10:48.299
Laurence Belson and his people
are using massive

10:48.343 --> 10:50.911
electrical currents to do
experiments on their brains.

10:50.954 --> 10:54.610
Well, I understand
interrogating them.

10:54.654 --> 10:58.266
But experimenting on them?
Why?

10:58.309 --> 11:00.442
No, there's something here
that doesn't add up,

11:00.485 --> 11:03.097
and I am not making a move
until I figure out what it is.

11:03.140 --> 11:05.360
[ Sighs ]

11:05.403 --> 11:07.231
Something happened
on that plane.

11:08.406 --> 11:10.147
And some of the passengers

11:10.191 --> 11:13.542
know things that...
no one else knows.

11:13.585 --> 11:15.979
You're gonna have to be
a hell of a lot more specific.

11:16.023 --> 11:19.504
I can't, because I don't
understand it myself, but we...

11:22.333 --> 11:24.553
...receive messages.
Impulses.

11:24.596 --> 11:26.642
It's why we gathered
before the plane blew up.

11:26.686 --> 11:29.993
How we found the Pyler sisters,
exonerated Radd's son.

11:30.037 --> 11:31.734
It's how Autumn found me.

11:32.996 --> 11:35.129
How much does
Laurence Belson know

11:35.172 --> 11:39.481
about this telepathy
or whatever it is?

11:39.524 --> 11:42.310
The first few days, they just
questioned us about the plane.

11:42.353 --> 11:45.356
And then some of us
got this vision.

11:45.400 --> 11:47.663
We just knew we had to
go to the plane,

11:47.707 --> 11:49.360
but they wouldn't let us.

11:49.404 --> 11:52.494
The next day, they told us
the plane had exploded.

11:52.537 --> 11:54.583
And then
everything changed.

11:54.626 --> 11:57.673
They started
these experiments.

11:57.717 --> 12:01.155
They called them treatments.
Twice a day.

12:01.198 --> 12:03.592
And every day,
they got more intense.

12:03.635 --> 12:05.550
Are you satisfied?
We have to go, now.

12:05.594 --> 12:07.814
Let -- Let me just wrap
my head around this.Jesus, Vance!

12:07.857 --> 12:09.990
Then stick your bureaucratic
head back in the ground

12:10.033 --> 12:12.296
and pretend it's not happening
because I am going in now,

12:12.340 --> 12:14.646
even if you're not!These people
are heavily armed.

12:14.690 --> 12:17.432
Why take that kind of risk?Because my son -- my --

12:17.475 --> 12:20.087
My son is channeling
the pain

12:20.130 --> 12:21.784
from one of the
missing passengers.

12:21.828 --> 12:24.656
How is that
even possible?

12:24.700 --> 12:26.571
How is any of this
possible?

12:26.615 --> 12:28.486
As soon as
the experiments start,

12:28.530 --> 12:30.227
Cal will feel
that torture.

12:30.271 --> 12:32.664
There is nothing I won't do
to protect my son.

12:32.708 --> 12:35.058
We have to go, now!

12:35.102 --> 12:38.279
♪♪

12:38.322 --> 12:40.629
Woman:
We're ready, sir.

12:42.326 --> 12:43.893
Oh, no.

12:43.937 --> 12:46.591
[ Beeping ]

12:46.635 --> 12:49.638
-Is everyone on?
-We're here.

12:49.681 --> 12:51.771
You're able to see
all the subjects?

12:51.814 --> 12:53.163
Man: We can see.

12:53.207 --> 12:55.905
The Major says proceed.
-Copy that.

12:55.949 --> 12:58.603
Okay, as you can see, we are
officially up and running again

12:58.647 --> 13:00.605
and are now commencing Phase Two

13:00.649 --> 13:03.130
of the Mirror Factor
test protocol.

13:03.173 --> 13:05.523
If everyone's set, I'll pass it
over to you, Doctor.

13:05.567 --> 13:08.439
We had mild but noticeable
sympathetic responses

13:08.483 --> 13:09.919
among some of the subjects

13:09.963 --> 13:11.921
with our initial testing
on Subject 3,

13:11.965 --> 13:14.968
so we'll now adjust up
to a base line of 40%

13:15.011 --> 13:17.797
on Subject 3 only.

13:17.840 --> 13:20.103
Female computerized voice:
Subject 3 only.

13:20.147 --> 13:23.846
[ Whirring, click, groaning ]

13:23.890 --> 13:27.284
Marked pain response
in Subjects 4 and 7,

13:27.328 --> 13:30.461
yet only Subject 3
is receiving stimulation.

13:30.505 --> 13:32.333
Adjust down
base line to zero.

13:32.376 --> 13:34.161
[ Whirring stops ]

13:34.204 --> 13:35.553
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:35.597 --> 13:37.860
These are our most
significant results yet.

13:37.904 --> 13:39.949
Man: But only two
others responded.

13:39.993 --> 13:41.821
That appears
to be correct.

13:41.864 --> 13:44.519
Can we try again
with an increased charge?

13:44.562 --> 13:46.956
Double it, please.

13:47.000 --> 13:49.741
Our normal protocol is a
six-hour downtime per charge.

13:49.785 --> 13:51.569
We don't know how
sequential testing cou--

13:51.613 --> 13:54.398
Let's try.
Go ahead. 80%.

13:54.442 --> 13:56.748
[ Whirring ]

13:59.708 --> 14:02.058
[ Electricity crackling ]

14:02.102 --> 14:04.017
[ High-pitched buzzing ]Aah!

14:04.060 --> 14:06.889
[ High-pitched buzzing ][ Groans ]

14:06.933 --> 14:08.412
[ High-pitched buzzing ][ Gasping ]

14:08.456 --> 14:10.023
[ High-pitched buzzing ]Ohh!

14:10.066 --> 14:11.676
What the hell?!

14:11.720 --> 14:14.201
[ Strained ]
They've started up again!

14:22.383 --> 14:23.993
[ Breathing sharply ]

14:24.037 --> 14:27.344
[ High-pitched buzzing stops ]What the hell was that?!

14:27.388 --> 14:29.694
Was that what you felt
at the lab?

14:29.738 --> 14:33.524
If we felt it, I can only
imagine what my son felt.

14:33.568 --> 14:35.004
[ Cellphone unlocks ]

14:35.048 --> 14:37.224
[ Cellphone ringing ]

14:37.267 --> 14:38.747
Hi, Dad.
Are you on your w--

14:38.790 --> 14:40.009
Is, uh, Cal okay?

14:40.053 --> 14:43.012
Yeah, and so am I.

14:43.056 --> 14:45.885
Can you check on Cal?

14:45.928 --> 14:48.365
Sure.

14:48.409 --> 14:51.716
[ Knocking] Cal, are you okay?

14:51.760 --> 14:54.545
Cal: I-I'm fine!He's fine.

14:54.589 --> 14:56.765
Can you make sure,
please?

14:56.808 --> 14:59.724
♪♪

14:59.768 --> 15:01.944
Cal: Do you mind?
I'm busy.

15:01.988 --> 15:05.600
He's totally fine.
Rude, but fine.

15:05.643 --> 15:07.210
[ Door closes ]

15:07.254 --> 15:09.299
[ Breathing rapidly ]

15:09.343 --> 15:16.089
♪♪

15:16.132 --> 15:17.394
Is Cal okay?

15:17.438 --> 15:20.310
For now.

15:20.354 --> 15:22.312
Enough proof?

15:22.356 --> 15:24.575
I will assemble
a tactical team.

15:24.619 --> 15:26.577
Good.
I'll meet you on site.

15:26.621 --> 15:28.231
No, not you. Look.

15:28.275 --> 15:30.146
I was military,

15:30.190 --> 15:32.496
but I am gonna be standing
behind a tactical unit.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.107
There's no way
I'm bringing in civilians.

15:34.150 --> 15:35.804
No, no, if I'm not there,
how will you know

15:35.847 --> 15:37.937
if the mission is affecting us,
affecting my son?

15:37.980 --> 15:40.113
I'm not gonna get in the way,
but I'm coming.

15:40.156 --> 15:41.505
So am I.

15:42.593 --> 15:44.856
If they're using my research,
you're gonna need me.

15:47.337 --> 15:50.384
I'll meet you
in ninety minutes.

15:50.427 --> 15:52.690
Turn off your cellphones.
Leave them here.

15:52.734 --> 15:55.302
All communications is through
the burners I gave you.

15:55.345 --> 15:57.521
They cannot know
we're coming.

15:59.045 --> 16:02.178
I'll text you
the rendezvous point.

16:02.222 --> 16:04.833
♪♪

16:04.876 --> 16:06.835
[ Door opens and closes ]

16:06.878 --> 16:08.663
So make sure you give it
a really good toss

16:08.706 --> 16:11.013
'cause the olive oil's kind of
settling on the bottom there.

16:11.057 --> 16:13.146
[ Doorbell rings ]Okay.
Oh, I will get the door.

16:13.189 --> 16:15.365
Please call Dad and make sure
he's getting home from work.

16:15.409 --> 16:17.237
Yes. Your dad.

16:17.280 --> 16:20.675
Cal! People are here!
Please come down!

16:20.718 --> 16:22.416
[ Ringing]

16:22.459 --> 16:24.505
Ben: You've reached Ben Stone.
Please leave a message.

16:24.548 --> 16:26.681
Hey, babe. Are you
on your way home?

16:26.724 --> 16:28.335
Call me.

16:28.378 --> 16:30.337
[ Beep ]

16:30.380 --> 16:31.599
Hey!

16:31.642 --> 16:34.036
-Hey! Hi!
-Oh, how's it going?

16:34.080 --> 16:35.690
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:35.733 --> 16:38.040
Hey. You okay?

16:38.084 --> 16:40.434
Yeah, it was nothing.
It was just a headache.

16:40.477 --> 16:43.089
That wasn't just
a headache, Mick.

16:43.132 --> 16:44.525
Let me help you.

16:44.568 --> 16:45.874
It's not your fight, Jared.

16:45.917 --> 16:48.790
[ Cellphone ringing ]

16:52.011 --> 16:53.534
Where did you get that?

16:53.577 --> 16:55.057
NSA guy. Vance.

16:55.101 --> 16:56.537
Vance, the guy who
wanted me to spy on you.

16:56.580 --> 16:58.060
-He's on our side now.
-So he says.

16:58.104 --> 16:59.627
No, he's risking
everything to help us.

16:59.670 --> 17:01.542
He's calling in a team.So where do we meet him?

17:01.585 --> 17:03.283
[ Chuckles, scoffs ]If that guy's
gonna be there,

17:03.326 --> 17:05.067
you better believe
I'm coming with you.

17:07.983 --> 17:09.724
I'll tell Vance
you're joining.

17:09.767 --> 17:11.595
Warehouse in Red Hook.

17:11.639 --> 17:13.597
And next time I see your mom,
remind me to ask her

17:13.641 --> 17:16.731
why her son
is so damn stubborn.

17:16.774 --> 17:18.559
Ben better
get here soon.

17:18.602 --> 17:20.909
These last few beers aren't
gonna drink themselves.

17:20.952 --> 17:22.954
[ Laughs ] I'm gonna
get these burgers on.

17:22.998 --> 17:24.826
Grace, do you have
any napkins?

17:24.869 --> 17:27.394
Uh, yes.
Just give me one sec.

17:27.437 --> 17:32.094
♪♪

17:32.138 --> 17:35.097
You've reached Ben Stone.
Please leave a message.

17:35.141 --> 17:37.012
Ben, this is the third message
I've left you.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.927
I'm starting to get worried.

17:38.970 --> 17:40.755
Can you please just let me know
you're all right?

17:40.798 --> 17:44.367
Mom. Mom! Mom!
They need to talk to Dad.

17:45.542 --> 17:47.414
Is Ben Stone here?

17:47.457 --> 17:49.851
No. I'm sorry.
He's at work.

17:49.894 --> 17:52.941
I assure you, ma'am,
he's not.

17:52.984 --> 17:54.421
His employment
was terminated

17:54.464 --> 17:57.119
as of 8:00 p.m.
yesterday evening.

17:57.163 --> 18:01.167
What? No, that's impossible.
Why?

18:01.210 --> 18:03.647
We really can't discuss the
details of the termination,

18:03.691 --> 18:06.607
but it is imperative
that we talk to Mr. Stone

18:06.650 --> 18:09.349
or his attorney
as soon as possible.

18:09.392 --> 18:11.002
His attorney?

18:11.046 --> 18:14.615
And I'm afraid we need to
collect his I.D. badge.

18:14.658 --> 18:23.319
♪♪

18:23.363 --> 18:32.023
♪♪

18:32.067 --> 18:40.728
♪♪

18:40.771 --> 18:42.077
Go.

18:42.121 --> 18:48.214
♪♪

18:48.257 --> 18:54.350
♪♪

18:54.394 --> 19:00.530
♪♪

19:00.574 --> 19:01.749
-Clear!
-All clear!

19:01.792 --> 19:04.186
-No one here, sir!
-All clear!

19:04.230 --> 19:06.536
-They're gone. All of them.
-What the hell?

19:06.580 --> 19:08.843
-...stand down. All clear.
-No sign of anyone!

19:08.886 --> 19:10.714
Man: Building's secure!

19:12.629 --> 19:15.806
Cal?

19:15.850 --> 19:19.941
Cal, Mom -- Mom
needs us right now.

19:19.984 --> 19:21.638
Cal.

19:21.682 --> 19:25.425
♪♪

19:25.468 --> 19:27.731
No. No, no, no. T-The missing
passengers were here.

19:27.775 --> 19:29.429
All the data pointed
to this location.

19:29.472 --> 19:31.431
The property records,
the cellphone pings --

19:31.474 --> 19:33.476
Ben, we looked everywhere.
They're not here.

19:33.520 --> 19:35.478
Maybe somebody
tipped them off.

19:35.522 --> 19:38.394
Well, maybe, they did.
You know, these people are
smart, but one false --

19:38.438 --> 19:40.831
Stop, everyone.
This is getting us nowhere.

19:40.875 --> 19:42.659
We have to find
these people.

19:42.703 --> 19:46.968
Where do we look?
We have noidea where they went.

19:47.011 --> 19:50.232
Cal: Dad!

19:50.276 --> 19:52.843
They're still here.

19:59.154 --> 20:01.243
Cal, what are you doing here?
Where's Mom?

20:01.287 --> 20:02.810
I had to come.
I left a note.

20:02.853 --> 20:05.291
No, you cannot be here.
This is crazy.

20:05.334 --> 20:06.901
How did you even --I took a bus.

20:08.294 --> 20:10.818
No one knows where
we are right now.

20:10.861 --> 20:13.473
I knew. It's like
the subway tunnels, Dad.

20:15.083 --> 20:17.259
Oh, my God.
Cal, you're burning up.

20:17.303 --> 20:19.783
No, Dad.
You don't understand.

20:19.827 --> 20:21.829
I'm supposed to
help you find them.

20:21.872 --> 20:23.787
They're right here.

20:23.831 --> 20:25.789
Cal, we turned the
warehouse upside down.
They're not in there.

20:25.833 --> 20:28.618
They're right here!

20:28.662 --> 20:36.800
♪♪

20:36.844 --> 20:38.976
Check between
those trees.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.500
Seriously?

20:40.543 --> 20:41.892
[ Exhales sharply ]

20:41.936 --> 20:43.851
I followed a headache --

20:43.894 --> 20:46.854
I may as well follow
a crayon drawing.

20:46.897 --> 20:51.206
♪♪

20:51.250 --> 20:52.686
Come on.
We got to get you home.

20:52.729 --> 20:55.254
No.
Youhave to help them.

20:55.297 --> 20:57.299
There's a whole team here, Cal.
Come on.

20:57.343 --> 20:59.040
They found something!

21:01.434 --> 21:04.872
You have to go, Dad. You're the
only one that can see them!

21:04.915 --> 21:06.308
Ben, it's a calling.

21:06.352 --> 21:09.311
"Who can see them"?
What do you mean, buddy?

21:09.355 --> 21:12.575
I don't know. All I know
is that you have to go!

21:12.619 --> 21:14.534
Go. I'll take him home.

21:14.577 --> 21:16.623
No, I'm waiting for Dad.

21:18.538 --> 21:20.061
Hurry!

21:20.104 --> 21:22.106
I'll keep him safe
in the car. Come on.

21:23.630 --> 21:26.720
Come on. Let's go!

21:26.763 --> 21:28.069
Keep him safe!

21:28.112 --> 21:30.245
Call Grace!

21:32.291 --> 21:33.901
Thanks.

21:35.119 --> 21:37.296
[ Flashlight clicks ]

21:40.255 --> 21:41.691
Mom, where's Dad?

21:41.735 --> 21:43.345
Honey, I don't want you
to worry about your dad.

21:43.389 --> 21:45.260
I don't care what
those people say.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.870
No, Mom, I'm not
worried about Dad, okay?
I'm worried about Cal.

21:46.914 --> 21:48.263
He's gone.

21:52.398 --> 21:54.748
Oh, my God.

21:54.791 --> 22:00.319
♪♪

22:00.362 --> 22:05.802
♪♪

22:05.846 --> 22:07.804
Jared:
What is this place?

22:07.848 --> 22:09.240
Vance:
Definitely wasn't on any map,

22:09.284 --> 22:11.155
but it looks like
an old coal cellar.

22:11.199 --> 22:14.376
There's a whole system
of tunnels down here.

22:14.420 --> 22:17.727
♪♪

22:17.771 --> 22:19.163
[ Softly ] Vance!

22:19.207 --> 22:23.472
I told you two to hang back.
This is dangerous.

22:23.516 --> 22:25.561
-I don't --
-Hey.

22:25.605 --> 22:35.266
♪♪

22:35.310 --> 22:36.659
[ Gun cocks ]

22:36.703 --> 22:43.144
♪♪

22:43.187 --> 22:46.321
NSA, drop your weapon!
Drop it!

22:46.365 --> 22:48.410
[ Gunfire ]

22:49.846 --> 22:52.153
Get the files!
Everything you can carry!

22:52.196 --> 22:53.633
Erasure protocol!

22:53.676 --> 22:55.374
[ Gunfire ]

22:55.417 --> 22:57.550
Neutralize. Do it!

22:57.593 --> 22:59.639
We can't leave
any evidence behind!

22:59.682 --> 23:02.990
[ Whirring, all groaning ]

23:03.033 --> 23:05.427
[ High-pitched buzzing ]

23:05.471 --> 23:07.690
[ Gunfire ]

23:21.487 --> 23:23.750
[ Gunfire continues ]

23:23.793 --> 23:26.840
[ Indistinct shouting ]

23:26.883 --> 23:30.757
♪♪

23:30.800 --> 23:32.411
[ All groaning ]

23:32.454 --> 23:34.935
My God.

23:34.978 --> 23:37.416
-Spread out!
-Move, move, move!

23:37.459 --> 23:41.028
Make it stop, please!
[ Grunts ]

23:41.071 --> 23:44.248
[ Electricity crackling ]

23:49.950 --> 23:52.561
We got to get them
out of here now!

23:54.476 --> 23:56.347
Freeze!

23:59.002 --> 24:01.701
You okay?

24:01.744 --> 24:04.443
Clarke:
Detach the leads!

24:06.357 --> 24:08.490
[ Gunfire ]

24:12.668 --> 24:15.541
[ High-pitched buzzing ]

24:15.584 --> 24:23.897
♪♪

24:23.940 --> 24:32.166
♪♪

24:32.209 --> 24:34.342
[ Gun cocks ]Vance: Belson! Stop!

24:36.518 --> 24:38.564
You're way out of
your depth, Director.

24:38.607 --> 24:40.000
Who you working for?

24:40.043 --> 24:42.132
Who has the funding to get
all this up and running

24:42.176 --> 24:43.612
and keep it all
under wraps?

24:43.656 --> 24:46.876
You clearly have no idea
who you're interfering with.

24:49.879 --> 24:52.360
Neither do you.[ Handcuffs clicking ]

24:52.403 --> 24:56.103
[ Electricity crackling ]

24:56.146 --> 25:00.107
♪♪

25:00.150 --> 25:01.804
[ High-pitched buzzing stops ]

25:01.848 --> 25:08.550
♪♪

25:08.594 --> 25:11.118
This way! Follow me!

25:11.161 --> 25:19.474
♪♪

25:19.518 --> 25:22.477
Which way?

25:22.521 --> 25:30.659
♪♪

25:30.703 --> 25:34.054
Lights. Follow --
Follow the lights.

25:34.097 --> 25:36.186
To the right.
What lights?

25:36.230 --> 25:38.188
You don't see
path lights?

25:38.232 --> 25:40.408
No. Oh, my God.

25:40.451 --> 25:43.542
Cal said you'd be
the only one to see them.

25:43.585 --> 25:45.021
He meant the lights.

25:47.676 --> 25:50.592
-Let's go.
-Yeah.

25:50.636 --> 25:59.340
♪♪

25:59.383 --> 26:08.088
♪♪

26:08.131 --> 26:10.743
I think we're
going in circles.

26:10.786 --> 26:12.396
Which way?

26:12.440 --> 26:14.485
Let's try the left.

26:14.529 --> 26:17.576
♪♪

26:17.619 --> 26:20.709
-You getting in?
-No, I can't.

26:20.753 --> 26:24.060
I found a remote property.
I'm going to take them there.

26:24.104 --> 26:25.584
They'll be safe with me.

26:25.627 --> 26:26.889
Be careful.

26:26.933 --> 26:28.499
Yeah.

26:28.543 --> 26:31.285
Man: We're clear.

26:32.460 --> 26:34.331
You okay?

26:34.375 --> 26:35.898
Where's Jared and Vance?

26:35.942 --> 26:38.335
They went to get Laurence
with a couple of Vance's guys.

26:38.379 --> 26:40.468
Take Cal home.
I'm gonna go check.

26:40.511 --> 26:42.035
Okay. Come on.

26:43.558 --> 26:46.169
[ Rumbling, explosion ]

26:46.213 --> 26:49.129
-Jared!
-Mick!

26:56.571 --> 27:00.444
[ Coughing ]

27:00.488 --> 27:03.143
[ Softly ] Cal.

27:03.186 --> 27:06.320
Cal. Cal!

27:06.363 --> 27:11.760
♪♪

27:11.804 --> 27:17.113
♪♪

27:17.157 --> 27:20.377
Cal. Cal!

27:20.421 --> 27:22.336
Cal!

27:22.379 --> 27:25.774
-[ Coughing ]
-Cal. Are you okay?

27:25.818 --> 27:27.341
I'm fine, Dad

27:28.821 --> 27:29.952
Mick!

27:29.996 --> 27:32.694
♪♪

27:32.738 --> 27:34.783
-Mick.
-[ Coughs ]

27:34.827 --> 27:37.568
There's tunnels under the
whole area. It's unstable.

27:37.612 --> 27:38.961
Come on.

27:39.005 --> 27:40.223
Okay?

27:42.182 --> 27:45.968
Hey. We got to go, okay?
We got to go!

27:46.012 --> 27:47.143
Come on.

27:47.187 --> 27:48.841
No. Take Cal and go.

27:48.884 --> 27:50.712
It's unsafe!
Mick, get in the car!

27:50.756 --> 27:53.323
Jared's still down there, Ben!
Jared is still down there!

27:53.367 --> 27:57.414
I'm not leaving him!
Just take Cal! Go! Go!

27:57.458 --> 28:01.375
♪♪

28:01.418 --> 28:03.203
[ Engine starts ]

28:03.246 --> 28:06.989
♪♪

28:07.033 --> 28:08.687
Jared!

28:08.730 --> 28:10.993
[ Rocks crumbling ]

28:11.037 --> 28:18.609
♪♪

28:18.653 --> 28:26.182
♪♪

28:26.226 --> 28:28.184
Jared!

28:28.228 --> 28:30.578
No, no. Come on.
Come on, Jared. Come on.

28:30.621 --> 28:32.623
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

28:32.667 --> 28:35.714
Come on. Please.
Please, please, please, please.

28:35.757 --> 28:38.064
Somebody help me!
Help me!

28:38.107 --> 28:43.634
Jared. Please don't do this.
No, no, no, no. Jared.

28:51.599 --> 28:53.732
Oh, my God. Cal.

28:53.775 --> 28:55.124
Grace, he's okay.

28:56.647 --> 28:59.433
You can't do that.
You can't leave like that.

28:59.476 --> 29:01.740
-He's fine.
-He is not fine.

29:01.783 --> 29:03.306
Come on. Let's get you
cleaned up, okay?

29:03.350 --> 29:05.961
-Grace.
-Just...stay away.

29:07.484 --> 29:11.401
♪♪

29:11.445 --> 29:13.403
[ Monitor beeping ]

29:13.447 --> 29:15.492
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:15.536 --> 29:24.501
♪♪

29:24.545 --> 29:26.112
Has he come to yet?

29:28.157 --> 29:30.333
How the hell did you two

29:30.377 --> 29:33.206
get mixed up in an
anti-terrorist op?

29:36.687 --> 29:38.298
We got
an anonymous tip.

29:38.341 --> 29:40.561
We didn't know what
we were walking into.

29:40.604 --> 29:43.825
Some good people
lost their lives.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.522
I knew one of them.

29:45.566 --> 29:48.699
Robert Vance, NSA.

29:48.743 --> 29:52.660
No, I saw him getting loaded
into the back of an ambulance.

29:52.703 --> 29:55.576
He didn't make it.

29:55.619 --> 30:00.668
♪♪

30:00.711 --> 30:05.673
♪♪

30:05.716 --> 30:08.589
But don't give up hope.

30:08.632 --> 30:10.417
He needs you.

30:10.460 --> 30:18.773
♪♪

30:18.817 --> 30:27.173
♪♪

30:27.216 --> 30:35.529
♪♪

30:35.572 --> 30:37.531
[ Monitor beeping ]

30:37.574 --> 30:44.581
♪♪

30:44.625 --> 30:51.719
♪♪

30:51.762 --> 30:55.070
I don't know who you are
or what you are,

30:55.114 --> 30:57.377
but I have listened to you.

30:57.420 --> 30:58.944
[ Sobs ]

30:58.987 --> 31:02.208
Listen to me, please.

31:02.251 --> 31:05.428
I can't lose him.
Please, I can't lose him.

31:05.472 --> 31:07.561
I can't lose him.

31:07.604 --> 31:09.389
[ Sobbing ]

31:09.432 --> 31:11.782
I can't lose you.
I can't lose him.

31:11.826 --> 31:13.915
Please don't go.
Please don't go.

31:13.959 --> 31:16.004
Please don't go.

31:17.440 --> 31:19.312
I know this all
sounds crazy --

31:19.355 --> 31:22.271
No, not crazy.
Horrifying.

31:22.315 --> 31:25.144
There were assault weapons
and explosions?!

31:25.187 --> 31:26.841
What were you thinking?

31:26.885 --> 31:29.975
I-I didn't bring him, Grace.
I was shocked when he showed up.

31:30.018 --> 31:32.934
Then why didn't you
bring him home immediately?

31:32.978 --> 31:35.067
He could've been
killed, Ben.

31:35.110 --> 31:36.764
You don't understand.
You weren't on the plane.

31:36.807 --> 31:38.635
But you have to trust me.

31:38.679 --> 31:41.247
Everything I am doing
is to protect Cal.

31:41.290 --> 31:43.597
After all we went through
with his cancer, I can't --

31:43.640 --> 31:46.643
You can't what?
You can't lose him?

31:47.993 --> 31:50.082
768.

31:50.125 --> 31:54.434
That's how many days I watched
cancer consume my little boy.

31:54.477 --> 31:57.089
Eight months.
That's how long it took me

31:57.132 --> 32:00.440
to file the death certificate
after the plane disappeared.

32:00.483 --> 32:04.966
1,430.

32:05.010 --> 32:07.186
You know what that was?

32:07.229 --> 32:09.797
The cost of
my son's gravestone.

32:09.840 --> 32:11.277
Grace.

32:11.320 --> 32:14.541
So please don't ever tell me
that I don't understand,

32:14.584 --> 32:19.198
because youdon't know what it's
like to have your child die.

32:19.241 --> 32:22.462
You're right. I am sorry.

32:22.505 --> 32:24.812
But don't you want me to do

32:24.855 --> 32:27.858
whatever it takes
to keep our son safe?

32:29.338 --> 32:31.645
Is that what you call
what happened this afternoon?

32:31.688 --> 32:33.908
Keeping him safe?

32:38.521 --> 32:44.223
I thought I could just ignore
the last five years of my life,

32:44.266 --> 32:48.053
that we could just...

32:48.096 --> 32:51.143
start over right where
we left off,

32:51.186 --> 32:56.496
because you were the same
even if I wasn't.

32:56.539 --> 32:59.151
You're not the same.

32:59.194 --> 33:03.894
I just --
I don't know you.

33:03.938 --> 33:09.770
And I don't -- I don't think
this is right anymore.

33:09.813 --> 33:18.779
♪♪

33:18.822 --> 33:27.744
♪♪

33:27.788 --> 33:29.920
[ Chuckles ]

33:29.964 --> 33:33.489
♪♪

33:33.533 --> 33:36.014
You're right.

33:36.057 --> 33:39.147
I can't give you what
you need...right now,

33:39.191 --> 33:42.585
what you...

33:42.629 --> 33:44.848
deserve.

33:44.892 --> 33:48.156
♪♪

33:48.200 --> 33:49.810
I'll go.

33:55.337 --> 33:57.818
But I need to
take Cal with me.

33:59.689 --> 34:02.301
How could you
even suggest that?

34:02.344 --> 34:06.957
I am the only one who can
keep him safe right now.

34:07.001 --> 34:11.440
I mourned my son

34:11.484 --> 34:13.834
for five years.

34:13.877 --> 34:17.359
I will never, never
let anyone

34:17.403 --> 34:21.972
take him away from me,
not ever again.

34:22.016 --> 34:23.844
You should go.

34:23.887 --> 34:32.287
♪♪

34:32.331 --> 34:40.817
♪♪

34:40.861 --> 34:43.690
[ Monitor beeping ]

34:43.733 --> 34:48.825
♪♪

34:48.869 --> 34:51.089
[ Sniffles ]

34:53.700 --> 34:55.310
[ Groans softly ]

34:55.354 --> 34:56.877
Jared. Jared.

34:56.920 --> 34:58.226
Ugh.

34:58.270 --> 35:00.185
Thank you, thank you,
thank you.

35:03.188 --> 35:05.233
-Hi.
-[ Laughs ] Hi.

35:05.277 --> 35:08.018
Hi. Hi.

35:08.062 --> 35:09.933
Lourdes is on her way.
I'll go -- I'll go get her.

35:09.977 --> 35:11.718
No, no, please.

35:15.635 --> 35:17.245
Stay with me.

35:17.289 --> 35:19.682
[ Julien Baker's
"Turn Out the Lights" plays ]

35:19.726 --> 35:23.512
♪♪

35:23.556 --> 35:25.123
Okay.

35:25.166 --> 35:31.216
♪ There's a hole in the drywall
still not fixed ♪

35:31.259 --> 35:36.177
♪ 'Cause I just haven't
gotten around to it ♪

35:36.221 --> 35:38.701
♪ And besides

35:38.745 --> 35:43.750
♪ I'm starting to
get used to the gaps ♪

35:43.793 --> 35:50.931
♪♪

35:50.974 --> 35:58.068
♪♪

35:58.112 --> 36:05.206
♪♪

36:05.250 --> 36:11.430
♪ But when I turn out
the lights ♪

36:11.473 --> 36:17.218
♪ When I turn out the lights

36:17.262 --> 36:23.485
♪ When I turn out the lights

36:23.529 --> 36:27.010
♪ Ohh

36:27.054 --> 36:29.926
♪♪

36:29.970 --> 36:34.148
♪ There's no

36:34.192 --> 36:36.846
♪ One

36:36.890 --> 36:39.153
♪ Left

36:39.197 --> 36:41.721
♪♪

36:41.764 --> 36:51.644
♪ Between myself

36:51.687 --> 36:53.298
[ Door opens and closes ]

36:53.341 --> 36:56.214
♪ And me

37:01.131 --> 37:02.524
Thought I might
find you here.

37:02.568 --> 37:04.483
Nowhere else to go.

37:04.526 --> 37:06.876
We'll find a place.

37:10.053 --> 37:12.534
It's awful about Vance.

37:14.754 --> 37:17.017
You know, I read
something online.

37:17.060 --> 37:21.369
It said his friends
called him "Bobby."

37:21.413 --> 37:23.328
-Bobby.
-[ Chuckles ]

37:23.371 --> 37:25.852
That does not suit him
at all.

37:25.895 --> 37:27.897
[ Laughs ]

37:29.943 --> 37:32.902
It sounds like Jared's through
the woods, though, right?

37:34.164 --> 37:35.688
I don't know.

37:35.731 --> 37:38.212
He knows about
the calling, so...

37:38.256 --> 37:40.345
You don't still believe
that telling people

37:40.388 --> 37:42.434
about the callings
is getting them killed?

37:42.477 --> 37:45.785
You told Vance, and...

37:45.828 --> 37:47.700
There was an explosion.

37:47.743 --> 37:50.137
It was an accident.

37:50.180 --> 37:51.878
And Vance
wasn't the only one

37:51.921 --> 37:53.227
that knew about the callings
down there.

37:53.271 --> 37:56.752
Jared did, too.
He didn't die.

37:59.320 --> 38:00.756
It's because...

38:00.800 --> 38:02.932
Because what?

38:04.630 --> 38:07.546
The callings
talk to us, Ben.

38:07.589 --> 38:08.808
This time, I talked back.

38:08.851 --> 38:10.984
I asked the callings
to save Jared.

38:13.334 --> 38:14.770
[ Scoffs ]

38:14.814 --> 38:17.904
How can you think, after
everything that's happened,

38:17.947 --> 38:23.388
that we have any control
whatsoever over this thing?

38:23.431 --> 38:25.912
It worked.

38:25.955 --> 38:27.479
Jared's gonna be okay,

38:27.522 --> 38:29.437
and that wasn't at all certain
last night.

38:29.481 --> 38:31.831
People get better, Mick,

38:31.874 --> 38:36.749
through no magic,
no prayer...

38:36.792 --> 38:40.274
or whatever you want to call it,
no callings.

38:40.318 --> 38:41.580
They just get better.

38:41.623 --> 38:43.582
You can deny it
all you want, Ben,

38:43.625 --> 38:45.279
but don't forget
that you told Grace,

38:45.323 --> 38:47.934
and if she had been
the one in the ICU,

38:47.977 --> 38:50.763
you would've been on your knees
just like I was.

38:50.806 --> 38:58.771
♪♪

38:58.814 --> 39:06.779
♪♪

39:06.822 --> 39:09.390
[ Door opens and closes ]

39:09.434 --> 39:15.875
♪♪

39:15.918 --> 39:19.444
I'm so sorry about
your friend Vance.

39:19.487 --> 39:21.315
I never should've
come here.

39:21.359 --> 39:22.882
None of this
is your fault.

39:22.925 --> 39:24.971
Everything you've done
to help so far

39:25.014 --> 39:28.148
has brought the whole thing
to an end.

39:28.191 --> 39:30.455
I have to go to work.
You gonna be okay?

39:30.498 --> 39:32.544
I'll be fine.
Thank you.

39:36.286 --> 39:38.724
You guys saved my life.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.247
[ Door opens and closes ]

39:40.290 --> 39:43.859
We saw the lab,
what you went through.

39:43.903 --> 39:47.385
But it's gone. You're safe.
You're one of us.

39:49.909 --> 39:51.214
Are you okay?
Are you hungry?

39:51.258 --> 39:52.825
[ Laughs ]

39:52.868 --> 39:54.392
We'll get you something.

39:54.435 --> 39:57.438
You guys are gonna get
so sick of me saying this,

39:57.482 --> 40:00.398
but thank you.

40:08.318 --> 40:12.671
[ Door opens and closes ]

40:20.113 --> 40:29.557
♪♪

40:29.601 --> 40:39.088
♪♪

40:39.132 --> 40:43.005
Just get him to trust you.
Be specific, but nothing useful.

40:43.049 --> 40:44.920
According to your
criminal record,

40:44.964 --> 40:46.966
this is your thing, right?

40:49.621 --> 40:51.274
Find out why he's
looking into us,

40:51.318 --> 40:53.973
what he knows,
and who he's working with.

40:54.016 --> 40:55.801
Is that perfectly clear?

40:55.844 --> 40:58.020
Yeah.

40:58.064 --> 41:00.936
♪♪

41:00.980 --> 41:03.461
I got it.

41:03.504 --> 41:10.119
♪♪

41:10.163 --> 41:16.778
♪♪

41:16.822 --> 41:18.780
Ben: Hey, buddy,
wanna take a break?

41:18.824 --> 41:20.565
-Can I have screen time?
-Yeah, sure.

41:28.660 --> 41:35.884
♪♪

41:35.928 --> 41:43.152
♪♪

41:43.196 --> 41:50.377
♪♪

41:50.420 --> 41:57.689
♪♪
